han make another weak hour cut from guesswork.\n\n**Decision:** Keep **11 UTC active** for now, do **not** cut it like 19 UTC, and start collecting copy-regime context in every new outcome so the next P2 pass can test whether 11 UTC losses cluster in specific disagreement / crowded-expensive / transition-noise states.\n\n**Next:** Once a few new tagged trades land with the new fields, re-run 11 UTC performance by `copy_alignment_regime`, `copy_suppression_reason`, and `v6_cooldown_tag=FIRST` versus non-first trades.\n\n## 2026-05-01 01:04 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 1] BTC whale consensus flipped decisively long while ETH and SOL stayed one-way short\n\n**Task:** Run a fresh Pillar 1 leaderboard scan, quantify notional consensus, and decide whether the old split-BTC read still held.\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive (`pm-bot`, `hl-bot`).\n- Rotation pointed to **P1**.\n- Fresh HL tracker printed **BTC 6L/2S, ETH 2L/6S, SOL 1L/7S**, but the bigger change was notional, not count.\n- Notional-weighted state is now:\n  - **BTC:** longs **$24.03M** vs shorts **$0.17M** ",
